@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 Inf is a replacement for my main use of Info...finding out how much space
is left on the disk. But Info gives free space in @{"Blocks" link "Units" 27} which is no good!
Inf gives an easily readable way of finding out how much space is left. You
can specify the units (@{"bytes" link "Units" 10}/@{"kilobytes" link "Units" 16}/@{"Megabytes" link "Units" 22}), and even @{"watch" link "watch" 0} the free
space continuously.


@{b}Features@{ub}

   - Get space left on disk by volume name, device name, directory name,
     filename, or even assign in several places at once!

   - 3 different @{"output formats" link "Output Formats" 0}

   - 3 different @{"output units" link "Output Units" 0} (2 can be selected)

   - @{"Watch" link "Watch" 0} Facility

   - Have info in a @{"Window" link "Window" 0} on any @{"public screen" link "PublicScreen" 0}


@{"Click Here for Usage" link "Usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

@{b} Inf@{ub} v2.2 (28.09.94) by Michael Askin
 @{"DEVICE/M" link "Device" 0},@{"WB" link "Output Formats" 0}/S,@{"B=BYTES" link "Output Units" 0}/S,@{"KB=KILO" link "Output Units" 0}/S,@{"W=WATCH" link "Watch" 0}/S,@{"WIN=WINDOW" link "Window" 0}/S,
 @{"PS=PUBLICSCREEN" link "PublicScreen" 0}/K,@{"QUIET" link "Quiet" 0}/S:

  Click here for @{"Understanding of program templates" link "ArgLists" 0}

@{"Device" link "Device" 0}

   Specify the device, volume, directory, file, or assign on the disk you
   want info. Allows multiple arguments.

@{"WB" link "Output Formats" 0}

   Use WorkBench output format

@{"Bytes" link "Output Units" 0}

   Show all sizes in bytes

@{"Kilo" link "Output Units" 0}

   Show all sizes in Kilobytes

@{"Watch" link "Watch" 0}

   Continually show the results

@{"Window" link "Window" 0}

   Show the results in a window. If multiple devices have been given then
   only the first is shown.

@{"Public Screen" link "PublicScreen" 0}

   Puts the window on to any public screen

@{"Quiet" link "Quiet" 0}

   Just prints the number of bytes left, nothing else (for use with
   scripts).
@endnode

