@node "errormessages" "Error Messages"
@{b}@{u}Error Messages@{ub}@{uu}

There are several error messages. Here is a list of error messages, and
their meaning.

@{i}Could not find device@{ui}

   The device/directory/file/assign name you specified does not exist or
   Inf could not get a lock on it.

@{i}Could not get info from "<a device name>"@{ui}

   The Amiga library function 'Info' is used to get information from the
   disk. If this fails in any way then this error message will appear.

@{i}Could not open window!@{ui}

   The window could not be opened. This could be due to many reasons, one
   of which is that there is not enough memory.

@{i}Could not find public screen!@{ui}

   A public screen name was specified but could not be found. Check the
   spelling or case of the screen name you are trying to open. You might
   get this error message if there is no default public screen (which is
   usually Workbench).

@{i}Could not get device name@{ui}

   The part of the program which finds out the proper name of a device has
   failed. Probably due to the specified name not existing. It will try to
   continue the program, but if the rest manages to work then the name of
   the disk will be the one given by the user.
@endnode

